Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has called for the support of those who want to ensure SA lives up to the values of ANC veterans like Nelson Mandela. DURBAN - With opposition parties, the South African Communist Party (SACP) and lobby groups expected to hold demonstrations against the recent Cabinet reshuffle, Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has called for the support of those who want to ensure the country lives up to the values of African National Congress (ANC) veterans like Nelson Mandela.A recording of Ramaphosa speaking at a weekend event in KwaZulu-Natal has come to light; in it, he tells the audience that the time of renewal is upon the country. The deputy president went off script on Saturday evening and told the audience at the dinner to remain hopeful and not be scared by the recent events in the country What is happening now, is a process that is going to trigger a renewal; that renewal that we all need. He says now is the time for the country to unite. What you are advised to do as citizens of this country, is to support the efforts that are going to be made by those who want to make sure that our country lives up to the values of Nelson Mandela. Ramaphosa s comments come at a time when there are divisions with the ANC s top leaders over President Jacob Zuma s recent Cabinet reshuffle.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)